Units MKSA (as Meter Kilogram Second Ampere)
--------------------------------------------

NEWTON: Force accelerating 1 Kg along 1m by s^-2 :   Kg m s-2

JOULE: Heat quantity able to do a displacement of 1 Newton on 1 m :  Kg m2 s-2

WATT: Heat transfer or power of 1 joule in 1 second :  Kg m2 s-3

PASCAL: Pressure of a 1 Newton force on 1 m2 :  Kg m-1 s-2

KELVIN:  -273.15 CELSIUS degrees  or ZERO ABSOLUTE TEMPERATURE 

CONDUCTIVITY:  w m-1 K-1

VOLUMIC MASS rho:  Kg m-3

SPECIFIC HEAT Cth:  J  Kg-1  K-1

SPECIFIC HEAT CAPACITY  rho x Cth:  J K-1 m-3

HEAT TRANSFER COEFFICIENT:  w m-2 K-1

HEAT FLUX DENSITY:  w m-2
